Distributed ledger
	Block
		Data - sender, reciever, amount
		Hash - fingerprint
		 - identify the block and all its content
		Hash of previous block - makes it secure

	Changing one block makes all the following invalid - 


	
	Proof of work.
		In order to not be able to temper the chain and temper all the other hashes
		Make it demand more computing power to manipluate the chain.
			
	P2P network - 
		Everyone gets a full copy of the block-chainl




		
